WEBVTT

00:16.755 --> 00:18.105
[Octavia]
We were all wondering

00:18.148 --> 00:20.846
if you poisoned Marcellus.

00:20.890 --> 00:22.413
I'm sorry, what?

00:22.457 --> 00:25.199
Your husband's
been seeing a slave.

00:25.242 --> 00:27.723
It's betrayal,
the whole secret life.

00:27.766 --> 00:30.291
I think this is payback
for Marcellus.

00:30.334 --> 00:32.075
And I didn't see it.

00:32.119 --> 00:34.121
-Do I know you?
-I'm Vilbia.

00:34.164 --> 00:35.426
And I'm the daughter
of Augustus.

00:35.470 --> 00:36.688
What do you need, Vilbia?

00:36.732 --> 00:38.038
An audience with Livia Drusilla.

00:38.081 --> 00:39.213
And what do you want with her?

00:39.256 --> 00:42.346
My son--
I want Gaius to adopt him.

00:42.390 --> 00:44.044
I need your support.

00:44.087 --> 00:44.870
I'm running for consul
this year.

00:44.914 --> 00:46.176
Expensive.

00:46.220 --> 00:47.395
[Tiberius] Domitius--

00:47.438 --> 00:49.614
he's ruthless, ambitious.

00:49.658 --> 00:51.964
He's the coldest thing
I've ever touched.

00:52.008 --> 00:55.272
Domitius is your direct rival
for any kind of power.

00:55.316 --> 00:58.014
Iullus has been intimate
with Julia,

00:58.058 --> 01:00.538
Iullus and I, this only happens
when I'm pregnant,

01:00.582 --> 01:02.192
so I always know
my husband's the father.

01:02.236 --> 01:04.977
Well, the party's over, Julia.
So is this.

01:05.021 --> 01:06.153
[Tycho] Porcia.

01:06.196 --> 01:07.676
You are my only family, Livia.

01:07.719 --> 01:09.069
I don't know
who else to turn to.

01:09.112 --> 01:10.548
But you need to leave Rome.

01:10.592 --> 01:12.420
Look after my daughter.

01:12.463 --> 01:14.465
-Oh! [laughs]
-[Livia] Go to Egypt...

01:14.509 --> 01:16.206
Don't forget me.

01:16.250 --> 01:17.947
...it's there we find out
who was behind the famine,

01:17.990 --> 01:20.515
for sure.

01:20.558 --> 01:21.429
I am pregnant...

01:21.472 --> 01:22.691
[screaming]

01:22.734 --> 01:25.389
...with your husband's son.

01:25.433 --> 01:26.608
[groans]

01:26.651 --> 01:27.696
Find out who did this.

01:27.739 --> 01:29.176
Whatever it takes.

01:29.219 --> 01:31.003
You betrayed me, my love.

01:31.047 --> 01:34.398
[Gaius] I never cared
that she killed Marcellus.

01:34.442 --> 01:37.749
I care that she got caught.

01:37.793 --> 01:38.663
I need you to do
something for me.

01:38.707 --> 01:39.925
Divorce?

01:39.969 --> 01:41.101
Exile.

01:41.144 --> 01:43.103
[Tiberius] She's been exiled.

01:43.146 --> 01:45.844
Without the marriage connection,

01:45.888 --> 01:48.064
we're meaningless to him.

01:48.108 --> 01:50.936
We'll never avenge
our grandfather

01:50.979 --> 01:53.461
and never restore the republic.

01:53.503 --> 01:57.639
[dramatic music plays]

02:00.990 --> 02:04.559
[applause]

02:13.220 --> 02:15.091
The office of Consul

02:15.135 --> 02:18.138
is the greatest honor
Rome can bestow.

02:18.181 --> 02:20.357
It is my honor tonight

02:20.401 --> 02:25.014
to introduce the winners
of this year's elections.

02:25.057 --> 02:27.451
Publius Cornelius Scipio!

02:27.495 --> 02:30.062
[applause]

02:30.106 --> 02:32.108
And Lucius Domitius Ahenobarbus.

02:32.152 --> 02:35.590
[applause]

02:39.246 --> 02:40.769
[indistinct conversations]

02:40.812 --> 02:43.031
Anything you need. Always.

02:45.904 --> 02:49.821
♪♪♪

02:49.865 --> 02:52.737
[indistinct conversations]

02:58.787 --> 03:01.268
Mother used to love
these election night parties.

03:01.311 --> 03:04.227
Bitching, backstabbing...

03:04.271 --> 03:06.142
plots.

03:08.188 --> 03:12.017
I never thought I'd say this,
but I'm starting to wonder

03:12.061 --> 03:13.845
whether she's coming back
from this.

03:16.370 --> 03:19.460
It's up to us now, brother.

03:25.683 --> 03:26.945
Everything.

03:26.989 --> 03:29.687
♪♪♪

03:34.257 --> 03:36.999
No point in being envious,
my love.

03:37.042 --> 03:40.916
If you'd taken my advice,
Domitius might be ash by now.

03:42.961 --> 03:45.399
Agrippa will be out of Rome
in the morning.

03:45.442 --> 03:46.878
I'm going to pop any day now.

03:46.922 --> 03:49.403
Might be our last chance
for a long time.

03:54.886 --> 03:56.671
[Marcella]
Congratulations, Consul.

03:56.714 --> 03:59.456
You said you'd think about it.

03:59.500 --> 04:03.112
Revenge on Livia
is your passion, not mine.

04:03.155 --> 04:04.287
There will never be
a better time.

04:04.331 --> 04:06.942
She's alone and weak...

04:06.985 --> 04:08.726
and out of Rome.

04:08.770 --> 04:11.468
She's already dead, Marcella.

04:11.512 --> 04:13.340
-You just haven't noticed.
-[man] Well done, Domitius.

04:13.383 --> 04:15.298
-Richly deserved.
-Thank you.

04:16.690 --> 04:18.082
[knocks]

04:18.127 --> 04:21.303
Augustus and Agrippa
won't live forever,

04:21.348 --> 04:23.306
and sadly,
your mother's gone.

04:23.350 --> 04:26.353
We need to plan
for what comes next,

04:26.396 --> 04:30.531
unless we want it
to be Domitius.

04:30.574 --> 04:32.010
What did you have in mind?

04:32.054 --> 04:34.448
A Triumvirate.

04:34.491 --> 04:37.189
Everything divided equally
between the three of us--

04:37.233 --> 04:38.321
power,

04:38.365 --> 04:40.976
land, and army.

04:42.586 --> 04:44.893
We'd have to liquidate Domitius.

04:44.936 --> 04:47.069
And his supporters.

04:51.029 --> 04:57.079
[indistinct conversation]

04:57.122 --> 05:00.038
[suspenseful music plays]

05:00.082 --> 05:03.128
♪♪♪

05:11.876 --> 05:14.966
I hope we don't have to
liquidate Iullus, too.

05:15.010 --> 05:18.753
[drums playing rapidly]

05:18.796 --> 05:21.146
[Domitius] My friends, can I
offer either of you a dancer?

05:21.190 --> 05:23.888
[Musca] No.
You can scrap the regulations

05:23.932 --> 05:26.108
which limit the height
of the tenement buildings.

05:26.151 --> 05:28.676
I still need to see Livia.

05:28.719 --> 05:30.504
She's still away.

05:30.547 --> 05:33.028
I don't know where she is.
What can I tell you?

05:33.071 --> 05:35.465
Try asking Piso.

05:35.509 --> 05:36.814
[Gaius]
Who's that with Domitius?

05:36.858 --> 05:38.990
Vilbia and his brother.

05:39.034 --> 05:42.472
Businessman,
sold votes to Domitius.

05:42.516 --> 05:47.216
-[drums continue beating]
-Thank you.

05:47.259 --> 05:50.001
You heard from your wife yet?

05:51.699 --> 05:54.571
Last letter I received
was from Egypt,

05:54.615 --> 05:57.182
and that was a while ago.

05:57.226 --> 06:00.316
It's been nearly
a year, brother.

06:00.360 --> 06:03.058
You must miss her.

06:03.101 --> 06:04.189
I know I do.

06:08.150 --> 06:11.196
I can't bear this ludicrous
charade for another moment.

06:11.240 --> 06:13.808
-What? No, Mother--
-Shh!

06:13.851 --> 06:15.244
-Mother!
-Quiet.

06:15.287 --> 06:18.116
[closes door]

06:18.160 --> 06:20.641
I know that nobody
is supposed to know

06:20.684 --> 06:23.339
what reallyhappened,

06:23.383 --> 06:27.517
and nobody's allowed
to mention it. [sighs]

06:27.561 --> 06:30.259
But you can't keep secrets
in this family.

06:30.302 --> 06:33.784
Everybody knows what Livia did
to that poor girl.

06:33.828 --> 06:37.135
And you were right to exile her.

06:37.179 --> 06:39.921
You know, it's not natural
for a man to be alone,

06:39.964 --> 06:43.968
and as your sister,
it is my duty to tell you.

06:44.012 --> 06:45.013
[sighs]

06:45.056 --> 06:47.711
You must divorce Livia now.

06:47.755 --> 06:51.280
You deserve to be free,
to get married again

06:51.323 --> 06:56.503
to some nice, young...
girl from a suitable family...

06:58.766 --> 07:00.942
...who can give you a son.
[sighs]

07:00.985 --> 07:05.468
Not opinions,

07:05.512 --> 07:08.079
endless scandal.

07:08.123 --> 07:08.950
[sighs]

07:20.614 --> 07:21.571
[door opens]

07:21.615 --> 07:23.530
I'll take that as a yes then.

07:27.925 --> 07:31.363
[serene music playing]

07:31.407 --> 07:33.278
[rooster crows]

07:34.671 --> 07:36.717
[exhales]

07:57.868 --> 07:58.869
[man groans]

08:05.485 --> 08:07.704
-[dishes clattering]
-[gasps]

08:07.748 --> 08:10.664
♪♪♪

08:23.938 --> 08:24.982
[rooster crows]

08:25.026 --> 08:27.115
[sighs]

08:28.595 --> 08:30.858
[clucks]

08:30.901 --> 08:32.554
Fuck.

08:32.599 --> 08:36.080
[theme music playing]

09:37.272 --> 09:38.882
[Piso sighs]

09:40.449 --> 09:43.626
All your life, Livia,

09:43.670 --> 09:48.544
you've lived with that oath
you made to your father.

09:48.588 --> 09:50.590
You were a child
when you made it.

09:51.939 --> 09:53.549
[sighs]

09:53.593 --> 09:56.987
Are you giving up on me, Piso,
or just the republic?

09:57.031 --> 09:58.815
Neither.

09:58.859 --> 10:03.124
But I know what a weight it is
you carry.

10:03.167 --> 10:05.648
And if you're weary of it all,
I'd understand,

10:05.692 --> 10:07.650
and your father
would understand.

10:07.694 --> 10:12.046
He'd want you to find
something else to live for.

10:14.701 --> 10:17.747
He would release you.

10:19.793 --> 10:20.620
Don't worry about me.

10:24.232 --> 10:27.235
I don't have to wake up...

10:27.278 --> 10:29.803
every morning and look perfect,

10:29.846 --> 10:33.894
and I don't have to clear up
some fucker's mess.

10:33.937 --> 10:38.376
I can be just...

10:38.420 --> 10:40.944
me.

10:40.988 --> 10:42.859
I'm happy.

10:42.903 --> 10:45.775
I don't miss it.

10:45.819 --> 10:47.690
[Piso]
This may be your life...

10:47.734 --> 10:49.953
from now on.

10:49.997 --> 10:53.435
Forever.

10:53.478 --> 10:55.437
Are you prepared for that?

10:57.221 --> 10:59.006
[scoffs] Nah.

10:59.049 --> 11:02.879
Gaius will come.

11:02.923 --> 11:05.360
Someone will come in the end,

11:05.403 --> 11:07.623
some fucker with a mess.

11:07.667 --> 11:10.670
They'll come.

11:11.975 --> 11:16.414
That slave
you're sleeping with...

11:16.458 --> 11:17.720
he's getting ideas.

11:23.247 --> 11:26.163
[moaning]

11:34.737 --> 11:36.260
Waiting.

11:36.304 --> 11:38.480
[panting]

11:38.523 --> 11:40.700
[chuckles] What?

11:40.743 --> 11:42.614
[exhales]

11:42.658 --> 11:45.226
We're always waiting
for something.

11:45.269 --> 11:47.750
Both of us.

11:47.794 --> 11:50.927
Waiting for this baby,
waiting for my husband to die.

11:50.971 --> 11:53.930
Waiting for my father to die.

11:53.974 --> 11:58.456
We're just... waiters.

11:58.500 --> 12:00.589
And people like Domitius
don't wait, Iullus.

12:00.632 --> 12:02.460
They take what they want.

12:05.115 --> 12:07.814
Oh, don't worry.

12:07.857 --> 12:10.120
I'm taking it.

12:14.821 --> 12:19.651
[Iullus groans softly]

12:19.695 --> 12:22.480
-[moaning]
-[gasps]

12:22.524 --> 12:24.352
-Ah! Ah!
-Gently.

12:24.395 --> 12:25.614
-[moans]
-Iullus, the baby.

12:25.657 --> 12:27.572
It's coming, now!

12:27.616 --> 12:28.791
Get the midwife!

12:28.835 --> 12:30.662
-Get me home! [groans]
-Fuck, oh...

12:30.706 --> 12:32.447
Ugh!

12:32.490 --> 12:34.275
Oh, please, let me live!

12:34.318 --> 12:35.755
Let me live!

12:35.798 --> 12:38.496
Ah! Ah!

12:38.540 --> 12:41.456
[dramatic music playing]

12:41.499 --> 12:43.414
♪♪♪

12:43.458 --> 12:45.939
[Prima] Dominus!

12:45.982 --> 12:48.332
[speaks indistinctly]

12:48.376 --> 12:54.904
[dramatic music builds]

12:54.948 --> 12:59.474
You are the most beautiful woman
in the whole fucking world!

12:59.517 --> 13:01.128
[baby crying]

13:01.171 --> 13:02.956
Fuck off, Agrippa!

13:02.999 --> 13:05.219
[baby crying]

13:05.262 --> 13:07.830
Four hours from start to finish!
I couldn't believe it.

13:07.874 --> 13:11.791
I love you, Julia.

13:11.834 --> 13:14.924
-I love you, too.
-I just heard!

13:14.968 --> 13:16.926
Another boy... [laughter]

13:16.970 --> 13:18.972
-Time for a drink.
-Always is.

13:19.015 --> 13:23.498
-Yes!
-[laughs]

13:23.541 --> 13:24.716
[sighs]

13:24.760 --> 13:30.635
[baby cooing]

13:30.679 --> 13:33.116
[Agrippa]
You're a grandfather.

13:33.160 --> 13:36.380
Again.

13:36.424 --> 13:38.818
Since it's you, I don't mind.

13:41.995 --> 13:43.735
Ah.

13:47.783 --> 13:50.133
Lucius Vipsanius Agrippa.

13:50.177 --> 13:53.093
Welcome to Rome.

13:56.052 --> 14:00.535
[serene music playing]

14:00.578 --> 14:02.145
-[Lucius gurgling]
-And you, little Gaius,

14:02.189 --> 14:05.061
you get some sleep
while you can.

14:05.105 --> 14:09.892
In 20 years, you'll be
drilling your cohort and...

14:09.936 --> 14:16.899
flogging the stragglers
in some camp somewhere.

14:16.943 --> 14:18.901
And you'll be married, Julila,

14:18.945 --> 14:21.469
with kids of your own,

14:21.512 --> 14:23.210
and your husband
stumbling round,

14:23.253 --> 14:24.733
pissed in the nursery.

14:24.776 --> 14:27.605
♪♪♪

14:27.649 --> 14:29.172
Hmm.

14:31.827 --> 14:33.437
And...

14:33.481 --> 14:35.700
If Drusus has any boys,

14:35.744 --> 14:37.877
[groans]

14:37.920 --> 14:40.227
I'll set you up
with one of them.

14:42.446 --> 14:45.449
[Lucius gurgling]

14:45.493 --> 14:47.799
Magic.

14:49.149 --> 14:51.325
-[indistinct conversation]
-[Julia] Let's get out of here.

14:51.368 --> 14:53.066
I want to go shopping so badly.

14:53.109 --> 14:54.458
[Antonia]
Were you actually having sex

14:54.502 --> 14:57.026
when the contractions started?

14:57.070 --> 14:58.332
-[Julia] Yes.
-[Antonia laughs]

14:58.375 --> 14:59.899
[Julia]
I was just about to come.

14:59.942 --> 15:01.813
It was so annoying.
I couldn't believe it.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.250
[Antonia laughs]

15:03.293 --> 15:04.555
And where was Agrippa?

15:04.599 --> 15:07.210
He was out of Rome all morning.

15:07.254 --> 15:09.125
We knew it might be
our last chance to be together,

15:09.169 --> 15:12.346
before I gave birth.

15:12.389 --> 15:14.652
-Ooh, the gods, I feel faint.
-Oh, no.

15:14.696 --> 15:17.568
[suspenseful music playing]

15:17.612 --> 15:20.528
♪♪♪

15:26.360 --> 15:27.970
Marcella.

15:28.014 --> 15:29.450
Have you seen the baby?

15:29.493 --> 15:31.800
[door opens]

15:31.843 --> 15:34.585
Uncle?

15:34.629 --> 15:36.674
[door opens]

15:38.981 --> 15:40.156
Uncle.

15:40.200 --> 15:44.682
[door opens]

15:44.726 --> 15:46.510
[door closes]

15:46.554 --> 15:48.251
Can I speak to you?

15:48.295 --> 15:50.732
Now. It's really important.

15:50.775 --> 15:53.430
♪♪♪

15:53.474 --> 15:55.824
[sighs]

16:02.265 --> 16:04.833
I hate to be the one
to have to tell you this,

16:04.876 --> 16:08.663
but sometimes one has to do
unpleasant things,

16:08.706 --> 16:11.013
and I consider it
nothing less than my duty

16:11.057 --> 16:13.624
to you and the family.

16:13.668 --> 16:15.583
Is this about your husband?

16:15.626 --> 16:17.150
No, Uncle,
It's not about Iullus.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.632
It's about Julia.

16:21.676 --> 16:25.985
♪♪♪

16:29.205 --> 16:33.862
[panting]

16:33.905 --> 16:36.256
Capria!
Where's the Domina?

16:36.299 --> 16:40.869
[indistinct conversations,
horse whinnies]

16:40.912 --> 16:43.785
Julia!

16:43.828 --> 16:46.701
Julia! He knows... Uncle.

16:46.744 --> 16:49.573
-He knows. Marcella told him.
-Told him what?

16:49.617 --> 16:51.575
She overheard you
and Antonia talking.

16:51.619 --> 16:53.403
She was outside your bedroom.

16:53.447 --> 16:55.362
What?

16:55.405 --> 16:57.973
About your affair with...
you know.

16:58.017 --> 17:00.671
I knew the minute I saw her face
that she was up to something.

17:00.715 --> 17:02.978
She was always such a sneak!

17:03.022 --> 17:05.589
-Did we mention his name?
-No.

17:05.633 --> 17:08.375
Uncle wanted to know,
but Marcella couldn't tell him.

17:08.417 --> 17:10.855
Agrippa will kill me.

17:10.898 --> 17:12.727
And Iullus and the children!

17:12.770 --> 17:15.208
-But they're all his!
-He won't believe that.

17:15.251 --> 17:16.599
Tell Antonia and Iullus
I have to go.

17:16.644 --> 17:18.819
No! You can't just run away!

17:18.863 --> 17:20.300
Not forever!

17:20.343 --> 17:22.388
Protect my children.
Swear on all the gods.

17:22.432 --> 17:24.826
I swear.

17:24.868 --> 17:28.786
[dramatic music playing]

17:28.830 --> 17:31.224
♪♪♪

17:36.794 --> 17:39.101
Livia! Livia!

17:39.145 --> 17:42.452
Piso says to tell you,
someone's come!

17:44.454 --> 17:46.021
So, these are dangerous people,

17:46.065 --> 17:47.979
connected in Rome
at a certain level,

17:48.023 --> 17:49.285
and very unpleasant.

17:49.329 --> 17:51.548
Even you need to be careful,

17:51.592 --> 17:54.812
especially now,
you're, er, unprotected.

17:54.856 --> 17:57.772
This is Livia Drusilla.

18:02.168 --> 18:04.083
Lady, my name is Vilbia,

18:04.126 --> 18:06.041
and I come humbly
to ask for your help.

18:14.049 --> 18:17.487
My grandfather came here
on a fishing boat.

18:17.531 --> 18:20.360
Rome, the city of opportunity.

18:20.403 --> 18:21.839
He couldn't read or write

18:21.883 --> 18:23.493
or speak Latin...

18:23.537 --> 18:28.019
but he was smart.
He knew how to work.

18:28.063 --> 18:30.413
And now my brother and I
have land and businesses

18:30.457 --> 18:32.850
and slaves.

18:32.894 --> 18:35.810
But, of course,
it's considered vulgar

18:35.853 --> 18:38.378
to make money through
hard work and talent,

18:38.421 --> 18:44.862
and I'll never be accepted,
politically or socially,

18:44.906 --> 18:46.212
without the right wife.

18:49.258 --> 18:52.653
Yours is one of the five
great families of Rome.

18:52.696 --> 18:56.047
With your influence
and personal connections,

18:56.091 --> 18:58.049
I was hoping
you would arrange my marriage

18:58.093 --> 19:01.009
to a woman of your class...

19:01.052 --> 19:03.664
in return for my silence.

19:06.710 --> 19:11.585
Everyone knows Augustus
has brought in legislation

19:11.628 --> 19:14.065
promoting
traditional family values.

19:14.109 --> 19:17.504
How disappointed he would be
to find out his stepson,

19:17.547 --> 19:20.289
Tiberius, once drunkenly
murdered a teenage girl

19:20.333 --> 19:22.639
in one of
my brother's brothels.

19:22.683 --> 19:25.729
Or that his other stepson,
Drusus,

19:25.773 --> 19:30.038
owes me hundreds of thousands
in gambling debts.

19:30.081 --> 19:32.823
And, yes,
I have his signed markers.

19:32.867 --> 19:38.612
As a woman, of course,
you might not know

19:38.655 --> 19:41.571
that gambling with dice
is illegal in Rome...

19:41.615 --> 19:42.964
by Augustus's own laws.

19:46.620 --> 19:49.449
I'll find you a wife.

19:49.492 --> 19:50.624
Don't make me come back.

19:50.667 --> 19:54.018
[dramatic music playing]

19:54.062 --> 19:57.239
[whispers]
Blackmailed by a pimp.

19:57.283 --> 20:01.809
Me, daughter of
Marcus Livius Drusus.

20:01.852 --> 20:03.027
Get my sons!

20:03.071 --> 20:05.247
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Is that wise?

20:05.291 --> 20:07.162
All this time
you've had no contact,

20:07.206 --> 20:09.120
for their sake,
and obviously you're still

20:09.164 --> 20:11.079
toxic, politically and socially.

20:11.122 --> 20:13.124
Get her sons.

20:13.168 --> 20:18.652
♪♪♪

20:18.695 --> 20:21.132
-[glass shatters]
-You malicious,

20:21.176 --> 20:23.396
stupid, little bitch!

20:23.439 --> 20:25.398
You have destroyed my daughter
and her marriage!

20:25.441 --> 20:26.921
[Marcella] What?

20:26.964 --> 20:30.011
How is it my fault
that she's a slut?

20:30.054 --> 20:31.491
She took my husband Agrippa,

20:31.534 --> 20:32.883
and now he isn't
good enough and...

20:32.927 --> 20:34.276
[scoffs]

20:34.320 --> 20:36.626
I'm supposed to feel
sorry for her.

20:36.670 --> 20:39.194
That spoiled
little princess bitch!

20:39.238 --> 20:40.413
It serves her right!

20:40.456 --> 20:42.066
Everybody has to bear
their sorrows,

20:42.110 --> 20:43.764
and you bear them
like a fucking Roman!

20:43.807 --> 20:46.288
-Fuck off.
-You do not turn on your family!

20:46.332 --> 20:48.159
[sighs]

20:48.203 --> 20:51.250
[door opens]

20:53.513 --> 20:55.689
Iullus.

20:55.732 --> 20:57.647
Augustus wants us.

21:06.613 --> 21:09.964
[crying]

21:10.007 --> 21:12.532
Who is it this time?

21:12.575 --> 21:15.056
It's Iullus.

21:15.099 --> 21:17.014
I cannot lose another son.

21:17.058 --> 21:18.494
And I cannot lose my daughter!

21:18.538 --> 21:20.844
She has disgraced the family!

21:20.888 --> 21:23.630
-How dare you blame her!
-Because she is to blame!

21:23.673 --> 21:25.675
She has fallen well

21:25.719 --> 21:28.025
beneath the required
standard, Scribonia.

21:28.069 --> 21:29.766
You have to go to your brother.

21:29.810 --> 21:32.291
You have to go to Livia.
Both of you.

21:32.334 --> 21:34.684
[Scribonia] What can she do?

21:34.728 --> 21:36.469
She's gone,
and she's never coming back.

21:36.512 --> 21:38.645
[sobbing]

21:38.688 --> 21:40.168
Gaius hates her.

21:40.211 --> 21:42.039
He won't listen
to anything she says,

21:42.083 --> 21:43.519
and what can she say anyway?

21:43.563 --> 21:45.521
They did it!

21:45.565 --> 21:47.393
She's not even allowed
to enter the gates of Rome.

21:47.436 --> 21:49.177
It's death if she does.

21:49.220 --> 21:50.613
-I thought you'd like that.
-[scoffs]

21:50.657 --> 21:52.528
Nobody even knows where she is.

21:52.572 --> 21:55.357
We know where she is.

21:55.401 --> 21:57.620
She killed your son!

21:57.664 --> 22:02.277
Octavia, she killed Marcellus.

22:02.321 --> 22:04.627
[thunder rumbles]

22:04.671 --> 22:07.543
[suspenseful music playing]

22:07.587 --> 22:11.417
♪♪♪

22:21.557 --> 22:25.735
My daughter has dishonored
her marriage to Agrippa.

22:25.779 --> 22:28.259
[thunder rumbling]

22:28.303 --> 22:31.741
Julia's run.

22:31.785 --> 22:33.874
But I will find her.

22:36.964 --> 22:40.707
If Agrippa finds out,

22:40.750 --> 22:43.623
he will divorce her.

22:43.666 --> 22:47.017
She will be publicly shamed.

22:47.061 --> 22:53.328
Iwill be publicly shamed.

22:53.372 --> 22:55.939
Our relationship
would never recover.

23:05.079 --> 23:09.388
Bring me the head
of Julia's lover.

23:11.477 --> 23:13.000
I want him found...

23:14.610 --> 23:16.743
Whoever he is.

23:16.786 --> 23:19.354
Whatever it takes.

23:22.183 --> 23:24.315
Of course.

23:28.581 --> 23:30.800
Does anyone know who it is?

23:30.844 --> 23:32.889
Honestly...

23:32.933 --> 23:33.847
I-I'm just shocked.

23:33.890 --> 23:36.110
[Drusus] It's hard to believe.

23:36.153 --> 23:39.853
We need to work together,
find this man.

23:39.896 --> 23:42.464
Our wives
are all close to Julia.

23:42.508 --> 23:45.032
One of them
will know who he is.

23:47.774 --> 23:51.299
♪♪♪

23:54.302 --> 23:57.392
-[door closes]
-Hey.

23:57.436 --> 23:59.046
We're with you.

23:59.089 --> 24:00.482
We're Romans.

24:00.526 --> 24:02.484
We hold
the fucking line together.

24:02.528 --> 24:04.704
He'll hunt me down like a dog.

24:04.747 --> 24:07.358
Antonia will never betray you.

24:07.402 --> 24:10.536
You should probably
get over there right now.

24:16.019 --> 24:18.544
Domitius.

24:18.587 --> 24:21.068
♪♪♪

24:21.111 --> 24:24.027
What are you doing here?

24:24.071 --> 24:26.377
Julia's lover--who is he?

24:26.421 --> 24:30.425
I don't know.

24:33.167 --> 24:40.391
You're her best friend.

24:40.435 --> 24:41.741
I know you know.

24:41.784 --> 24:45.832
Give me his name.

24:45.875 --> 24:47.573
We know them.

24:47.616 --> 24:50.837
-It must be someone we know.
-Ow! You're hurting me!

24:50.880 --> 24:54.318
-Who is he?
-Ow, my finger! No...

24:54.362 --> 24:56.407
No. She was too terrified
of anyone finding out,

24:56.451 --> 24:57.800
I swear on all the gods,
she wouldn't tell me.

24:57.844 --> 24:59.498
She wouldn't even tell me.

24:59.541 --> 25:01.108
-You're lying!
-[bone cracks]

25:01.151 --> 25:02.239
Ow! Aah, aah!

25:02.283 --> 25:03.589
-Who is he?
-No...

25:03.632 --> 25:05.112
-Who is he?
-[sobbing]

25:05.155 --> 25:06.766
Domitius, please, please.

25:06.809 --> 25:08.028
-Domitius, I'm...
-Who is he?

25:08.071 --> 25:09.029
[Antonia] He's...

25:09.072 --> 25:10.552
[Domitius groans]

25:10.596 --> 25:12.293
[panting]

25:12.336 --> 25:14.077
-[Domitius groans]
-[thuds]

25:14.121 --> 25:16.558
Iullus, no! Iullus! No.

25:16.602 --> 25:18.560
Brother, no. No!

25:18.604 --> 25:20.910
[gasping]

25:20.954 --> 25:23.347
♪♪♪

25:23.391 --> 25:25.611
[Antonina] What's happened?

25:25.654 --> 25:27.395
Fuck, I nearly
fucking killed him.

25:27.438 --> 25:29.049
It's okay, it's okay.

25:29.092 --> 25:30.790
Fuck.

25:30.833 --> 25:33.009
It's happening!

25:33.053 --> 25:35.621
-The terrible thing.
-[retches]

25:35.664 --> 25:38.319
♪♪♪

25:48.285 --> 25:50.418
My wife seems to
have disappeared.

25:59.209 --> 26:01.168
I see you knew.

26:05.651 --> 26:07.000
I will deal with it.

26:07.043 --> 26:10.569
With what, brother?

26:10.612 --> 26:13.441
With what will you deal?

26:13.484 --> 26:16.400
♪♪♪

26:21.449 --> 26:23.103
Where...

26:23.146 --> 26:24.931
is...

26:24.974 --> 26:26.410
my...

26:26.454 --> 26:27.542
wife?

26:30.371 --> 26:33.417
It is my understanding...

26:33.461 --> 26:35.289
Julia has...

26:38.814 --> 26:40.599
...dishonored her marriage...

26:42.426 --> 26:44.559
...and her family.

26:47.867 --> 26:50.739
"Dishonored"?

26:50.783 --> 26:54.351
And I will deal with it.

26:59.530 --> 27:02.664
With whom...

27:02.708 --> 27:08.409
has she dishonored it?

27:08.452 --> 27:11.630
I will deal with this.

27:14.197 --> 27:17.331
She is not to be touched.

27:17.374 --> 27:18.680
I don't kill women.

27:20.203 --> 27:24.164
Men, though...

27:24.207 --> 27:26.166
different matter.

27:26.209 --> 27:31.519
She is the bond between us
that cannot be broken.

27:32.738 --> 27:34.435
There will be no divorce.

27:34.478 --> 27:36.219
It would shame my family.

27:36.263 --> 27:38.047
And what about my family?

27:41.268 --> 27:43.400
I will deal with her.

27:43.444 --> 27:46.229
I want her...

27:46.273 --> 27:47.927
and the man...

27:47.970 --> 27:49.537
by tomorrow night.

27:51.278 --> 27:53.149
After that, it's over.

27:56.718 --> 27:57.806
If you divorce her...

27:59.765 --> 28:01.723
...we're finished.

28:01.767 --> 28:05.684
I know.

28:05.727 --> 28:08.382
♪♪♪

28:27.096 --> 28:30.056
I'm not tired.

28:30.099 --> 28:30.970
Aren't you sleepy?

28:31.013 --> 28:32.798
[Antonia] Agrippa.

28:32.841 --> 28:35.017
-Get out.
-No.

28:35.061 --> 28:36.323
We won't.

28:36.366 --> 28:38.194
-We swore we'd protect them.
-Get out!

28:38.238 --> 28:41.284
-Out! Get out!
-[all clamoring]

28:41.328 --> 28:43.896
Get out! Get out!

28:43.939 --> 28:46.072
[Lucius crying]

28:46.115 --> 28:46.986
[Vipsania] Father...

28:47.029 --> 28:50.946
[Lucius crying]

28:50.990 --> 28:51.947
Give him to me.

28:51.991 --> 28:53.993
-He's my brother.
-No.

28:54.036 --> 28:58.693
[crying continues]

28:58.737 --> 29:00.608
He's my brother.

29:00.651 --> 29:01.827
[Octavia] Agrippa!

29:01.870 --> 29:03.742
[crying continues]

29:10.618 --> 29:11.967
Agrippa, please!

29:12.011 --> 29:13.664
[Lucius crying]

29:13.708 --> 29:14.970
[weapon clanks]

29:15.014 --> 29:17.277
[sobbing]

29:17.320 --> 29:20.889
-[Lucius crying]
-[whispers] Go, go.

29:23.544 --> 29:24.545
[sobs]

29:26.155 --> 29:27.853
[Piso] Livia.

29:27.896 --> 29:29.942
Someone else has come.

29:29.985 --> 29:33.641
And unless I'm going blind,
it's a fucker with a mess.

29:33.684 --> 29:36.644
[thunderclap]

29:36.687 --> 29:37.645
Livia?

29:40.039 --> 29:43.651
[rooster crows]

29:48.395 --> 29:50.484
[sighs] Why are you still here?

29:50.527 --> 29:51.833
I told you I can't help.

29:51.877 --> 29:53.574
Please.
I don't care about myself,

29:53.617 --> 29:55.445
but if they find out
about Iullus,

29:55.489 --> 29:57.099
he'll have to take his own life.

29:57.143 --> 29:59.362
Well, Agrippa
might kill him first.

29:59.406 --> 30:01.147
Livia, I am begging you.

30:01.190 --> 30:03.149
I told you to end it with Iullus
years ago.

30:03.192 --> 30:05.368
Now you get caught.
What do you want me to do?

30:10.286 --> 30:13.333
You can stay here for now,
but that's all.

30:13.376 --> 30:15.030
"That's all"?

30:15.074 --> 30:16.902
-I'll be exiled.
-Well, you get used to it.

30:16.945 --> 30:18.599
You owe us, Livia!

30:18.642 --> 30:20.862
When everyone was saying
you killed Marcellus,

30:20.906 --> 30:22.385
me and Iullus,
we stood up for you!

30:22.429 --> 30:24.039
Livia, she's here.

30:26.346 --> 30:28.565
Well, I have my own problems.

30:28.609 --> 30:30.045
Stay hidden.
He'll send soldiers.

30:39.707 --> 30:41.622
I'm not running.

30:41.665 --> 30:43.363
[weapon clanking]

30:43.406 --> 30:44.103
Not from this.

30:48.585 --> 30:51.240
I am going to see Livia.

30:58.465 --> 31:00.902
-Porcia.
-Cousin.

31:00.946 --> 31:03.470
I thought you were never
gonna speak to me again.

31:03.513 --> 31:05.820
Well, you weren't
straight with me.

31:05.864 --> 31:07.909
I was in a difficult position.

31:07.953 --> 31:10.216
Underneath Crassus
with your legs open.

31:12.871 --> 31:14.873
I heard you've been traveling.

31:16.396 --> 31:17.919
[scoffs]

31:17.963 --> 31:20.748
How have you been?

31:20.791 --> 31:22.532
You must know that I'm living
under the charity

31:22.576 --> 31:26.058
of my great uncle, Junius.

31:26.101 --> 31:28.930
Oh, is it true
what they say about him?

31:28.974 --> 31:30.018
Worse.

31:30.062 --> 31:31.715
He's completely impotent

31:31.759 --> 31:33.717
and makes me submit
to cunnilingus.

31:33.761 --> 31:37.112
Yep. Debases himself
like a slave.

31:37.156 --> 31:39.071
What's it like?

31:39.114 --> 31:40.289
[Porcia] Cunnilingus?

31:40.333 --> 31:44.250
Well, Junius is 82,

31:44.293 --> 31:47.993
but I'm just a poor widow,
so there it is.

31:51.648 --> 31:54.477
I got you a husband,
if you want.

31:54.521 --> 31:57.219
-Is that why you sent for me?
-Your age.

31:57.263 --> 32:00.440
Healthy,
good-looking and rich.

32:00.483 --> 32:02.703
But?

32:02.746 --> 32:04.792
He's a businessman.

32:07.969 --> 32:09.753
I will pay you well,

32:09.797 --> 32:12.800
and the marriage
will buy me some time.

32:16.108 --> 32:18.545
Will it buy me
some forgiveness?

32:21.287 --> 32:23.332
Stay to dinner. Hmm?

32:23.376 --> 32:24.594
[exhales]

32:26.683 --> 32:28.250
[lowered voice]
I just want you to kill him.

32:28.294 --> 32:30.861
You're supposed to be
the mediator.

32:30.905 --> 32:32.820
Kill him later, then.

32:38.608 --> 32:41.002
Thank you both for coming.

32:41.046 --> 32:43.265
Iullus?

32:43.309 --> 32:45.354
Hmm.

32:45.398 --> 32:48.140
I was wrong to interfere.

32:48.183 --> 32:49.750
Forgive me.

32:49.793 --> 32:52.796
I thought that I could
help you talk to my sister.

32:52.840 --> 32:57.366
She'll return to your house
this morning.

32:57.410 --> 32:59.803
For what it's worth,

32:59.847 --> 33:03.155
she's the only person in this
family incapable of lying.

33:03.198 --> 33:05.853
She doesn't know
who Julia was with.

33:05.896 --> 33:08.769
Domitius?

33:08.812 --> 33:10.553
[Domitius]
Our fathers were friends.

33:10.597 --> 33:13.469
-They fought together.
-And died together.

33:18.474 --> 33:20.215
When all this is over,

33:20.259 --> 33:22.478
we should talk about the future,
you and me.

33:22.522 --> 33:24.698
Rome needs leaders.

33:24.741 --> 33:29.268
Let's do that.

33:29.311 --> 33:31.009
Off you go, then.

33:36.884 --> 33:38.059
[sighs]

33:40.627 --> 33:42.020
[Domitius] Nothing yet.

33:42.063 --> 33:44.979
[Iullus] Apologies from Drusus
and Tiberius.

33:45.023 --> 33:47.634
They left before dawn.

33:47.677 --> 33:50.071
They might have a lead on Julia.

33:50.115 --> 33:52.160
I had to tell Agrippa.

33:52.204 --> 33:56.469
We have until tonight
to find Julia.

33:56.512 --> 33:58.514
She will give us the man.
We will give him to Agrippa.

33:58.558 --> 34:00.647
It's my only shot
at making this right.

34:00.690 --> 34:04.346
Marcella has given us
a list of people

34:04.390 --> 34:06.783
who might be hiding Julia.

34:06.827 --> 34:10.091
You two will organize the search
with Strabo and the Praetorians,

34:10.135 --> 34:12.092
my authority,

34:12.137 --> 34:14.878
but nobody can know
what you're looking for.

34:14.922 --> 34:18.099
Domitius,

34:18.143 --> 34:21.233
there's a house I want you
to search personally.

34:29.154 --> 34:30.893
Drusus.

34:30.938 --> 34:33.331
Julia.

34:35.551 --> 34:36.509
[horse whinnies]

34:36.552 --> 34:38.206
How's Iullus?

34:38.250 --> 34:39.164
Well, he's busy looking
for himself

34:39.206 --> 34:40.382
so Agrippa can kill him.

34:40.426 --> 34:41.949
Tiberius.

34:41.992 --> 34:43.820
-Well, how does she think he is?
-[Julia] Well, fuck you!

34:43.864 --> 34:45.648
I'm glad we killed
your stupid, fucking terrapin!

34:46.996 --> 34:48.085
Fuck!

34:56.355 --> 34:57.573
[Drusus]
We got your message, Mother.

34:57.617 --> 35:01.447
Piso told us about Vilbia.

35:01.490 --> 35:02.970
We're both very sorry.

35:03.013 --> 35:05.668
[chuckles]

35:05.712 --> 35:07.931
Sorry?

35:09.324 --> 35:10.238
[Livia sighs]

35:17.027 --> 35:20.205
Oh. I missed you.

35:20.248 --> 35:22.990
I missed you.

35:26.515 --> 35:30.215
Oh, fuck it. You know,
I was no kind of mother.

35:30.258 --> 35:32.869
Babies are boring.
So are children.

35:34.523 --> 35:37.178
And I loved... [sighs]
parties and politics,

35:37.222 --> 35:39.006
but I mean, who doesn't?

35:41.400 --> 35:44.098
And I hated housework, too.

35:44.142 --> 35:48.407
All that...Roman matron shit.

35:48.450 --> 35:50.060
Is that so bad?

35:50.104 --> 35:52.715
Livia! Soldiers!

35:52.759 --> 35:55.370
They're searching the house.

35:55.414 --> 35:58.025
Stay here, out of sight,
all of you.

35:58.068 --> 36:00.158
[cup clatters]

36:05.424 --> 36:06.860
[Domitius] Livia.

36:06.903 --> 36:09.341
I'm glad to see you well.

36:09.384 --> 36:11.299
[Livia] Domitius.

36:11.343 --> 36:12.996
-What's going on?
-[Domitius laughs]

36:13.040 --> 36:15.085
Looking for Julia, apparently.

36:15.129 --> 36:18.045
Caesar wishes his daughter
returned to him today

36:18.088 --> 36:21.004
to avert
a severe political difficulty.

36:21.048 --> 36:24.573
If she's not back by nightfall,

36:24.617 --> 36:26.227
her personal slaves

36:26.271 --> 36:30.188
will be interrogated
under torture.

36:30.231 --> 36:33.669
They will give him
the name of Julia's lover.

36:33.713 --> 36:36.194
Wow.

36:36.237 --> 36:37.891
But why are you telling me this?

36:37.934 --> 36:41.199
Honestly, I have no idea.

36:41.242 --> 36:44.202
But Augustus
asked me to mention it

36:44.245 --> 36:45.899
if I happened to bump into you.

36:45.942 --> 36:48.249
[suspenseful music plays

36:48.293 --> 36:50.947
How's your wife?

36:50.991 --> 36:53.776
Antonia's well, thank you.

36:56.083 --> 36:57.911
And I'm sure
we both look forward

36:57.954 --> 37:01.088
to seeing you back in Rome...
soon.

37:01.131 --> 37:04.831
Hmm. As do I.

37:09.836 --> 37:12.142
Well, send her my love.

37:12.186 --> 37:15.102
♪♪♪

37:21.151 --> 37:23.502
-[footsteps retreat]
-[under breath] Fuck.

37:23.545 --> 37:26.200
[Marcella] Wait here.

37:26.244 --> 37:27.897
How could you do this?

37:27.941 --> 37:29.986
Well, I didn't ask her
to betray her husband.

37:31.553 --> 37:34.426
[Soldier] Take it all off.

37:34.469 --> 37:36.689
Everything off.

37:36.732 --> 37:39.561
[Antonina] What's going on?
We wait for the Dominus.

37:39.605 --> 37:42.564
There's no need for that.

37:42.608 --> 37:45.132
Their clothes will remain on.

37:45.175 --> 37:47.917
Analysis.

37:47.961 --> 37:51.443
Julia's slaves
will give up Iullus.

37:51.486 --> 37:55.316
There's now no scenario
in which he survives,

37:55.360 --> 37:58.711
which simplifies your plans
for the succession.

37:58.754 --> 38:00.669
It might have to come to that
in the end, anyway.

38:00.713 --> 38:04.107
-[sighs]
-What?

38:04.151 --> 38:08.155
Iullus thinks he's going to
share power with me and Drusus.

38:08.198 --> 38:10.679
What?

38:10.723 --> 38:15.336
He certainly won't like us
handing it back to the Senate.

38:15.380 --> 38:17.860
Otherwise, the beneficiary
of this mess is Domitius.

38:17.904 --> 38:19.122
[scoffs] Of course.

38:19.166 --> 38:21.777
With you in exile
and Agrippa estranged,

38:21.821 --> 38:24.345
a space opens up
right next to Augustus.

38:24.389 --> 38:27.217
And we don't want that, do we?
Mother?

38:28.915 --> 38:33.223
If anyone can get Agrippa
to back off, it's you.

38:33.267 --> 38:34.703
[Piso] Am I missing something?

38:34.747 --> 38:37.227
Is Julia not the fucker
with the mess

38:37.271 --> 38:39.969
that we were hoping for
that gets you back in the game,

38:40.013 --> 38:41.841
remind your husband
that you're still alive?

38:41.884 --> 38:44.452
Why should I?
Why should I help Julia?

38:44.496 --> 38:47.455
Hmm? Her mother put me here.

38:47.499 --> 38:48.587
You helped with that yourself.

38:48.630 --> 38:51.154
[Drusus]
And Iullus is one of us!

38:51.198 --> 38:52.765
-[rapid footsteps approach]
-[Ursa] Livia.

38:57.552 --> 39:00.425
[chickens clucking]

39:03.253 --> 39:04.298
[horse blustering]

39:18.399 --> 39:20.053
So, you're aware
of the situation?

39:22.316 --> 39:23.665
Yeah.

39:27.365 --> 39:30.803
Iullus was
a beautiful little boy.

39:30.846 --> 39:32.848
Image of his father.

39:32.892 --> 39:36.243
Sometimes even now,
I feel like I'm seeing a ghost.

39:40.769 --> 39:43.381
He is just my stepson.

39:43.424 --> 39:48.124
But he is...

39:48.168 --> 39:50.910
He's the only son I have now.

39:50.953 --> 39:58.439
[mournful music playing]

39:58.483 --> 40:03.096
You are the only one
that can move my brother

40:03.139 --> 40:05.141
and control Agrippa.

40:07.317 --> 40:09.189
Yeah, I know.

40:09.232 --> 40:10.712
-I know.
-Hmm.

40:12.148 --> 40:15.282
You owe me, Livia.

40:15.325 --> 40:17.023
You owe me this.

40:21.636 --> 40:24.160
I don't know how.

40:24.204 --> 40:27.642
I don't.

40:27.686 --> 40:30.210
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

40:31.820 --> 40:37.260
[dramatic music plays]

40:37.304 --> 40:44.485
[panting]

40:44.529 --> 40:48.097
♪♪♪

40:58.325 --> 41:00.196
Oh.

41:02.851 --> 41:04.679
Oh, right.

41:07.334 --> 41:08.161
Right.

41:10.729 --> 41:15.821
[door creaks open]

41:15.864 --> 41:16.735
What?

41:16.778 --> 41:18.519
[Iullus] Nothing.

41:18.563 --> 41:19.868
We've been out
looking for Julia.

41:19.912 --> 41:21.870
Oh, stop it.

41:21.914 --> 41:22.958
It's not fair.

41:27.354 --> 41:28.964
I don't know why I did it.

41:29.008 --> 41:32.838
I didn't think. I just did it.

41:32.881 --> 41:33.795
Now everyone hates me.

41:37.843 --> 41:39.540
Yes.

41:47.069 --> 41:48.549
[Livia] Are you ready?

41:48.593 --> 41:52.074
[Livia sighs]

41:52.118 --> 41:53.859
There's no other way.

41:53.902 --> 41:55.643
You must go to your father
and confess.

41:55.687 --> 41:58.385
You must tell him everything.

41:58.428 --> 42:01.649
If you don't, your slaves
will betray Iullus anyway.

42:01.693 --> 42:04.173
There must be blood.

42:04.217 --> 42:06.393
The men will have it,
Agrippa will have it.

42:06.436 --> 42:09.918
You can still save yourself
and your marriage.

42:09.962 --> 42:12.573
Your father will forgive you
because he has to.

42:12.617 --> 42:16.142
He cannot allow
a divorce with Agrippa.

42:16.185 --> 42:18.927
So, you just go and tell them
exactly what I told you.

42:18.971 --> 42:20.668
Tiberius will go with you.

42:20.712 --> 42:22.844
Can't it be Drusus?

42:22.888 --> 42:25.760
Oh, he has his own mess
to clear up.

42:27.893 --> 42:29.895
Don't worry.

42:29.938 --> 42:31.766
[horse blusters]

42:33.463 --> 42:35.074
Right.

42:35.117 --> 42:38.773
You, um...

42:38.817 --> 42:42.603
Porcia--she has agreed
to marry Vilbia for the family.

42:42.647 --> 42:45.171
You will take her back to Rome
and arrange it.

42:45.214 --> 42:48.740
-Now?
-Right now.

42:48.783 --> 42:52.352
♪♪♪

42:54.267 --> 42:55.616
Yes.

42:55.660 --> 42:59.359
[dog barking]

42:59.402 --> 43:01.274
[gate opens]

43:03.972 --> 43:06.148
No sign of Julia.

43:06.192 --> 43:08.586
-Livia?
-[doors close]

43:08.629 --> 43:09.935
She was there, yes.

43:09.978 --> 43:13.199
What did she say?

43:13.242 --> 43:16.376
She asked after my wife.

43:16.419 --> 43:19.205
[exhales deeply]

43:19.248 --> 43:26.604
We're waiting for Agrippa.

43:28.518 --> 43:30.651
-[woman whimpers]
-[exhales deeply]

43:30.695 --> 43:33.611
[serene music playing]

43:33.654 --> 43:41.749
♪♪♪

43:50.149 --> 43:52.760
Will they make it back
by nightfall?

43:58.723 --> 44:01.247
Just about.

44:01.290 --> 44:04.206
[indistinct conversations]

44:04.250 --> 44:05.512
That should be it.
Write it down.

44:05.555 --> 44:06.818
[Drusus] Vilbia!

44:06.861 --> 44:08.820
Drusus!

44:08.863 --> 44:11.561
-My mother sends you a wife.
-That was fast.

44:11.605 --> 44:15.174
My mother's very efficient,
and she always keeps her word.

44:15.217 --> 44:17.480
This is Porcia,

44:17.524 --> 44:19.004
daughter of
the Senator Marcus Porcius Cato,

44:19.047 --> 44:22.834
and a close relative of ours.

44:22.877 --> 44:24.139
She's a widow,

44:24.183 --> 44:25.488
and desperate to get away
from her guardian

44:25.532 --> 44:27.012
who always treats her badly.

44:27.055 --> 44:28.535
My mother will pay the dowry.

44:28.578 --> 44:30.015
Can she have children?

44:30.058 --> 44:32.844
I gave my first husband
two sons.

44:32.887 --> 44:34.149
They both died young.

44:34.193 --> 44:35.585
And you will marry me?

44:35.629 --> 44:39.415
I will.

44:39.459 --> 44:40.590
Her guardian's in Rome
expecting you now.

44:40.634 --> 44:43.550
Now?

44:43.593 --> 44:45.508
My mother wants the terms
of the marriage contract

44:45.552 --> 44:47.685
agreed in principle tonight,

44:47.728 --> 44:49.425
so there's no further
misunderstandings

44:49.469 --> 44:51.166
between our families.

44:51.210 --> 44:54.474
I'll take care of everything.

44:54.517 --> 45:00.436
[indistinct conversations]

45:00.480 --> 45:03.526
We're going to be relatives,
you and I.

45:03.570 --> 45:06.529
[Drusus] I might
pay you back one day.

45:06.573 --> 45:08.706
[laughter]

45:16.670 --> 45:20.326
[suspenseful music playing]

45:20.369 --> 45:23.416
♪♪♪

45:30.553 --> 45:32.294
Well, if you're going
to do it, do it.

45:32.338 --> 45:34.732
[slaves whimpering]

45:34.775 --> 45:36.690
[woman] No, no. Please, no.

45:36.734 --> 45:38.605
[woman crying]

45:38.648 --> 45:40.041
[woman] No!

45:40.085 --> 45:42.304
-[woman] Help me.
-That won't be necessary.

45:45.394 --> 45:46.221
[Tiberius] Stepfather.

45:46.265 --> 45:49.747
Agrippa.

45:49.790 --> 45:53.402
Julia's back,
of her own free will,

45:53.446 --> 45:55.448
and asks humbly
for your forgiveness.

45:57.406 --> 46:00.888
She swears before the gods...
her children are Agrippa's.

46:00.932 --> 46:04.283
Her brief and only disgrace

46:04.326 --> 46:08.026
began during
her most recent pregnancy.

46:15.990 --> 46:17.557
I want his name.

46:17.600 --> 46:20.908
♪♪♪

46:20.952 --> 46:23.041
Please...

46:23.084 --> 46:26.609
♪♪♪

46:33.878 --> 46:36.445
[crying]

46:40.101 --> 46:41.624
Who is it?

46:41.668 --> 46:46.455
[crying]

46:48.066 --> 46:49.545
Tell him.

46:49.589 --> 46:55.595
[sobbing]

46:55.638 --> 46:58.511
[suspenseful music builds]

46:58.554 --> 47:00.469
♪♪♪

47:02.602 --> 47:03.908
[door opens]

47:06.649 --> 47:08.260
[Drusus]
...towards the dowry.

47:13.787 --> 47:15.571
[groans]

47:24.145 --> 47:26.321
-[body thuds]
-[Porcia] Fuck.

47:29.759 --> 47:31.805
Wedding's off.

47:34.503 --> 47:36.897
Excuse me.

47:36.941 --> 47:40.118
[panting]

47:40.161 --> 47:43.077
I'll send someone to clear up.

47:49.779 --> 47:52.347
[Domitius] I had no idea
it was Vilbia.

47:52.391 --> 47:56.656
I barely know the man.
I don't know what to say.

47:56.699 --> 47:58.266
You could always say sorry
for bringing someone like that

47:58.310 --> 48:02.009
into our house,
given the consequences.

48:02.053 --> 48:04.533
This...

48:04.577 --> 48:06.492
stays in the family.

48:08.146 --> 48:09.538
Forever.

48:09.582 --> 48:11.018
Of course, Augustus.

48:11.062 --> 48:16.154
Thank you, Tiberius, Iullus.

48:22.769 --> 48:29.384
[suspenseful music playing]

48:29.428 --> 48:31.082
-What the fuck?
-[Tiberius] Leave us.

48:31.125 --> 48:32.648
[Julia] Livia.

48:32.692 --> 48:34.912
[Iullus chuckles] Of course.

48:37.653 --> 48:39.394
You didn't deserve it.

48:43.877 --> 48:45.792
[sighs]

48:45.835 --> 48:47.925
I'm really sorry, Iullus.

48:50.797 --> 48:53.713
[lowered voice]
I never regret a moment.

48:56.977 --> 48:58.109
[sighs]

48:58.152 --> 49:01.068
♪♪♪

49:04.550 --> 49:08.032
You had everything you wanted,
and you threw it all away.

49:08.075 --> 49:10.512
I had everything you wanted.

49:10.556 --> 49:12.340
Maybe that's why.

49:19.869 --> 49:25.136
Oh! Oh, my... Oh!

49:25.179 --> 49:27.355
It's all right.
Someone's coming to clear up.

49:27.399 --> 49:31.229
[panting]

49:32.578 --> 49:34.449
Oh...

49:36.538 --> 49:39.454
[gentle music playing]

49:39.498 --> 49:42.414
♪♪♪

50:18.580 --> 50:22.932
[horse whinnies]

50:25.065 --> 50:27.285
[exhales]

50:27.328 --> 50:28.590
-Go on, then!
-[Aelina] Daddy?

50:28.634 --> 50:29.983
[Tycho laughs] Ah!

50:30.027 --> 50:31.376
-[Aelina] Daddy!
-[laughter]

50:31.419 --> 50:33.334
[Tycho laughs]

50:33.378 --> 50:35.728
[groans]

50:35.771 --> 50:38.078
Oh, so you hadn't forgotten me.

50:38.122 --> 50:39.601
[sighs]

50:39.645 --> 50:40.472
I had.

50:40.515 --> 50:42.604
[laughter]

50:42.648 --> 50:44.389
What took you so long?

50:44.432 --> 50:46.913
Oh...

50:46.956 --> 50:49.872
[mellow music playing]

50:49.916 --> 50:52.614
♪♪♪

50:58.142 --> 51:04.409
[both laugh]

51:04.452 --> 51:07.629
It was Domitius
behind the famine.

51:07.673 --> 51:10.415
As you suspected.

51:10.458 --> 51:12.156
Can we prove it?

51:12.199 --> 51:14.723
Well, the proof died
while we were talking to him.

51:14.767 --> 51:16.812
[sighs]

51:16.856 --> 51:18.336
Welcome back, Tycho.

51:18.379 --> 51:20.555
[Piso] What do they want?

51:20.599 --> 51:24.255
[horses approaching]

51:56.722 --> 52:00.291
[whinnies and nickers]

52:10.562 --> 52:11.780
Gaius.

52:22.530 --> 52:23.966
I missed you.

52:28.797 --> 52:34.063
Oh... same.

52:34.107 --> 52:36.762
[exhales deeply]

52:36.805 --> 52:40.157
♪♪♪

52:48.034 --> 52:50.863
She's fucking done it.

52:50.906 --> 52:52.081
We're back.

53:01.090 --> 53:03.745
[both panting]

53:03.789 --> 53:07.271
[Gaius]
Thank you for finding Julia.

53:07.314 --> 53:11.100
Well, Julia's a free spirit.

53:11.144 --> 53:14.408
She hates other people's rules.

53:14.452 --> 53:17.063
She is absolutely your daughter.

53:17.106 --> 53:22.155
It's not her I'm worried about.

53:22.199 --> 53:26.725
It's Agrippa.

53:26.768 --> 53:27.856
[exhales deeply]

53:30.598 --> 53:35.081
Has he ever spoken
about adopting his sons?

53:35.124 --> 53:37.518
[panting]

53:37.562 --> 53:40.347
-Agrippa?
-Yeah.

53:40.391 --> 53:42.219
No.

53:42.262 --> 53:46.048
Well, he probably thought
you might refuse.

53:46.092 --> 53:48.181
He knows it's a lot to ask.

53:48.225 --> 53:51.140
A special honor...

53:51.184 --> 53:53.230
which would bind you together.

53:53.273 --> 53:57.059
[exhales deeply] Again.

53:57.103 --> 53:58.713
[exhales deeply]

54:02.326 --> 54:03.457
[exhales deeply]

54:08.462 --> 54:09.985
[exhales]

54:16.035 --> 54:17.384
[sighs]

54:17.428 --> 54:20.300
[suspenseful music playing]

54:20.344 --> 54:23.260
♪♪♪

54:57.555 --> 55:00.471
[indistinct conversation]

55:04.605 --> 55:07.565
[Gaius] Agrippa, Julia.

55:07.608 --> 55:10.437
[laughter,
indistinct conversation]

55:17.444 --> 55:22.884
Tonight we celebrate
the adoption of my grandsons,

55:22.928 --> 55:26.061
the sons of Agrippa,

55:26.105 --> 55:28.150
Gaius...

55:28.194 --> 55:29.456
and Lucius.

55:33.547 --> 55:37.246
One day
they will join Domitius,

55:37.290 --> 55:38.726
Iullus,

55:38.770 --> 55:40.554
Tiberius,

55:40.598 --> 55:42.513
and Drusus...

55:42.556 --> 55:47.953
in shaping the future of Rome.

55:49.563 --> 55:51.870
Family.

55:51.913 --> 55:52.740
-Family.
-Family.

55:52.784 --> 55:55.047
-Family.
-[all] Family.

55:55.090 --> 55:57.615
[laughter]

55:57.658 --> 55:59.051
[man] Wine's good.

55:59.094 --> 56:02.359
[indistinct conversation]

56:02.402 --> 56:03.490
-[door opens]
-Oh, no.

56:03.534 --> 56:15.197
♪♪♪

56:15.241 --> 56:17.591
Livia.

56:19.158 --> 56:22.422
[Agrippa]
Well, thank fuck for that.

56:22.466 --> 56:23.945
[laughter]

56:23.989 --> 56:27.122
The cockroach you can't squash
with your sandal.

56:27.166 --> 56:29.168
[man] We'd cut the role
of Senate.

56:29.211 --> 56:34.086
It wasn't Vilbia
Julia was sleeping with.

56:34.129 --> 56:36.305
Who was it, then?

56:36.349 --> 56:37.481
Exactly.

56:37.524 --> 56:41.963
[indistinct conversations
continue]

56:48.013 --> 56:49.928
It was fun while it lasted.

56:49.971 --> 56:52.452
No, it wasn't.

56:52.496 --> 56:56.761
My Lord, the Chief Vestal
is here with your will.

56:56.804 --> 56:59.328
Excuse me.
I'll get rid of her.

56:59.372 --> 57:05.117
♪♪♪

57:06.901 --> 57:09.077
-Gaius.
-Turia.

57:09.121 --> 57:11.253
-Good to see you.
-Welcome.

57:11.297 --> 57:13.560
[Turia] We have brought you
the will, as requested.

57:13.604 --> 57:16.737
Is he changing his will?

57:16.781 --> 57:22.003
Agrippa's sons are next in line
to succeed, suddenly.

57:22.047 --> 57:26.138
A sacrifice I had to make.

57:26.181 --> 57:28.270
We need to talk tomorrow.

57:32.492 --> 57:38.019
[indistinct conversations,
laughter]

57:38.063 --> 57:39.630
[lowered voice]
It took you long enough

57:39.673 --> 57:42.763
to come through on our deal.
-[sighs]

57:42.807 --> 57:45.636
-Nothing in it for me.
-[chuckles]

57:45.679 --> 57:49.596
Some people might think
you were kidding.

57:49.640 --> 57:54.949
No one who knows me.

57:57.822 --> 58:02.217
[laughs]

58:06.221 --> 58:09.007
[theme music playing]
